<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Stead1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Stead,</orth> subst. 1) place which another had or might have; preceded by <cit><quote>in:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.206" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 4, 206</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.207" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.192" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 192</bibl> <cit><quote>(were you in my s.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 1, 6</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>(--s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 85</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>(--s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 3, 26</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) use, help: <cit><quote>the help of one stands me in little s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 6, 31</bibl></cit>.
